1
00:01:34,153 --> 00:01:35,514
You must sense it...

2
00:01:37,378 --> 00:01:39,140
through your body,
through your feelings...

3
00:01:40,173 --> 00:01:41,673
when your living experience...

4
00:01:41,866 --> 00:01:44,247
level after level...

5
00:01:45,831 --> 00:01:47,872
right into the heart of it.

6
00:02:02,121 --> 00:02:04,570
Any chance of getting a lesson, sir?

7
00:02:08,209 --> 00:02:09,025
Ohhh, but...

8
00:02:11,396 --> 00:02:12,689
you may not know...

9
00:02:13,871 --> 00:02:16,864
but this is a solemn and serious matter.

10
00:02:26,818 --> 00:02:28,247
Just call me Shivas.

11
00:02:31,481 --> 00:02:33,454
Go ahead, they'll understand.

12
00:02:35,506 --> 00:02:36,799
Stick your bum out.

13
00:02:37,906 --> 00:02:39,335
Keep this straight...

14
00:02:39,493 --> 00:02:44,527
My name's Michael Murphy. I hope I'm not
intruding, but Shivas invited me to dinner-

15
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:46,162
Well, now Mr. Murphy,

16
00:02:46,218 --> 00:02:48,755
you wouldn't have done that if
you didn't have a good reason.

17
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:53,047
Don't worry, the Badman often
brings his play partners her to our place.

18
00:02:53,051 --> 00:02:54,684
Peter, my wife Agatha...

19
00:02:54,687 --> 00:02:56,664
welcome to our good camp Blaithe.

20
00:02:56,693 --> 00:02:58,689
What have you done with
our unpredictable friend?

21
00:02:58,720 --> 00:02:59,987
Me? I, uh...

22
00:03:00,039 --> 00:03:03,724
Ahh, don't tell me...he's out there waiting for the
moon to rise or communing with his higher self.

23
00:03:03,764 --> 00:03:06,064
This is Dr. Julian Lange.

24
00:03:06,089 --> 00:03:08,089
Ahh...Mr. Murphy.

25
00:03:08,114 --> 00:03:12,014
so, I hear the man brought you
through the eye of the needle?

26
00:03:12,039 --> 00:03:15,139
-Excuse me?
-Oh, he's just messing with you.

27
00:03:15,164 --> 00:03:17,164
These are the Greens...

28
00:03:17,189 --> 00:03:20,389
they've come from Cornwall to study
the ecology here at Burningbush.

29
00:03:20,414 --> 00:03:25,414
Adam, here teaches cosmic ecology
at London's free university.

30
00:03:25,439 --> 00:03:28,339
And Eve teaches creative
environmental writing.

31
00:03:28,364 --> 00:03:33,864
They've got this wonderful new theory
of <i>evolution</i> and golfing links.

32
00:03:55,865 --> 00:03:58,462
I do want to hear what you
and Shamus talk about...

33
00:03:59,772 --> 00:04:03,276
I really do. I mean this
is why I'm going to India.

34
00:04:03,327 --> 00:04:04,969
I'm going to learn about this stuff.

35
00:04:06,391 --> 00:04:09,310
I hope to be a writer someday, actually.

36
00:04:09,473 --> 00:04:12,229
But right now I'm finishing
my studies in philosophy.

37
00:04:23,832 --> 00:04:24,980
I'll do it.

38
00:04:50,551 --> 00:04:52,968
This is the most famous
golf course in the world.

39
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:57,156
This is where it all began...

40
00:04:57,234 --> 00:04:59,934
I've come all the way from California.
I'm only here for the day.

41
00:05:02,392 --> 00:05:06,057
I've played Pebble my whole life, but I've
always dreamed of playing Burningbush.

42
00:05:06,082 --> 00:05:08,785
Put me with the best player on that list.

43
00:05:11,708 --> 00:05:13,108
I can match up with anyone...

44
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,966
if not better.

45
00:05:17,380 --> 00:05:18,024
[MICHAEL] Hello.

46
00:05:18,787 --> 00:05:20,631
The starter told me to join you two.

47
00:05:30,797 --> 00:05:31,681
Shivas Irons.

48
00:05:35,331 --> 00:05:36,351
Michael Murphy.

49
00:05:37,224 --> 00:05:38,249
Balie McIver.

50
00:05:41,989 --> 00:05:45,118
Let's try a few shots for
the set up swing...

51
00:05:46,617 --> 00:05:49,678
and a few shots for
through gravity...

52
00:05:50,948 --> 00:05:53,085
and then a few to score.

53
00:06:26,746 --> 00:06:27,788
Good shot.

54
00:06:28,882 --> 00:06:31,127
How did you know to hit it there?

55
00:06:32,048 --> 00:06:34,361
That's the best line to the green.

56
00:06:35,327 --> 00:06:36,007
Just luck.

57
00:06:37,921 --> 00:06:41,509
(Shivas Singing)

58
00:06:45,994 --> 00:06:47,791
[SHIVAS] How you doin'?

59
00:06:47,825 --> 00:06:48,603
[SHIVAS] Good to see ya...

60
00:06:48,630 --> 00:06:50,331
[AGATHA] Men loving men...

61
00:06:50,619 --> 00:06:52,184
that's what golf is.

62
00:06:52,932 --> 00:06:57,182
[AGATHA] It's a way you've found to get
together yet still maintain a proper distance.

63
00:06:58,985 --> 00:07:01,828
But don't get me wrong,
you're not like us women...

64
00:07:01,870 --> 00:07:05,407
or Italians all hugging
embracing each other.

65
00:07:05,662 --> 00:07:07,516
You need to feel your separate love.

66
00:07:08,245 --> 00:07:09,061
Just look...

67
00:07:09,495 --> 00:07:13,181
You won't come home on time when you're with the boys.
I've learned that over the years.

68
00:07:14,329 --> 00:07:17,735
The love you feel for your
friends is too strong for that.

69
00:07:19,235 --> 00:07:21,016
And all those gentlemanly rules...

70
00:07:21,902 --> 00:07:24,318
why they're the proper rules of affection.

71
00:07:24,777 --> 00:07:28,412
All the waiting and the "oohing
and aahing" over your shots...

72
00:07:28,485 --> 00:07:32,433
and this one's drive and that one's
putt and the other one's gorgeous swing...

73
00:07:32,715 --> 00:07:34,750
what is all that, but love?

74
00:07:36,017 --> 00:07:38,266
Men loving men...that's what golf is.

75
00:07:38,923 --> 00:07:41,061
I like your swing, Michael.

76
00:07:41,997 --> 00:07:47,575
Your not a professional, now are you...trying
to sneak up on us for a wee bit, eh?

77
00:07:48,340 --> 00:07:50,789
Uh, just an amateur passing through.

78
00:07:51,590 --> 00:07:53,219
Where are you headed?

79
00:07:53,486 --> 00:07:57,819
India...to a place you've probably
never heard of called Pondicherry.

80
00:07:59,924 --> 00:08:03,017
[SHIVAS] In the ashram of
Sri Aurobindo, perhaps?

81
00:08:04,789 --> 00:08:06,684
[MICHAEL] Oh my God, you know it.

82
00:08:07,508 --> 00:08:09,005
No one does back home.

83
00:08:09,914 --> 00:08:13,792
[SHIVAS] Nor do they here.
             Nor do they here.

84
00:08:15,082 --> 00:08:16,032
Let's tee it up..

85
00:08:19,253 --> 00:08:21,308
Any chance of getting a lesson, sir?

86
00:08:24,808 --> 00:08:25,976
Oh, but...

87
00:08:28,245 --> 00:08:29,742
you may not know...

88
00:08:30,664 --> 00:08:33,589
but this is a solemn and serious matter.

89
00:08:42,527 --> 00:08:44,320
And just call me Shivas.

90
00:08:57,455 --> 00:09:00,448
Alright...2 or 3 birdies on the par fives...

91
00:09:00,633 --> 00:09:02,198
maybe 1 or 2 more...

92
00:09:04,358 --> 00:09:06,943
that should give me a shot at a 72.

93
00:09:06,981 --> 00:09:07,933
If not better.

94
00:09:14,998 --> 00:09:17,291
Just hold on now there, Michael.

95
00:09:18,243 --> 00:09:19,318
Wait your turn.

96
00:09:36,744 --> 00:09:41,760
I propose that we all take a turn
describing the game of golf.

97
00:09:41,882 --> 00:09:43,175
Each one telling...

98
00:09:43,609 --> 00:09:47,895
exactly what this endlessly
mysterious game is really about.

99
00:09:48,584 --> 00:09:54,936
It's time we done justice to the subject,
and this is just the crowd to do it.

100
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:55,460
Now...

101
00:09:55,638 --> 00:09:58,750
Michael, you will remember it all...

102
00:09:59,481 --> 00:10:00,637
for posterity.

103
00:10:01,652 --> 00:10:03,982
Peter, your the host...begin.

104
00:10:04,051 --> 00:10:06,538
No, Agatha is.
This is her party.

105
00:10:06,991 --> 00:10:09,196
Well, then Agatha...begin.

106
00:10:09,298 --> 00:10:11,815
Nope, Peter's the one with the ideas.

107
00:10:11,890 --> 00:10:13,251
Well, then, Peter...

108
00:10:13,698 --> 00:10:16,837
You'll not be gettin' any fancy theories from me.

109
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:19,131
And I'll keep my speech short.

110
00:10:22,187 --> 00:10:26,813
I'm saying my farewell to the game...
I've suffered enough with it.

111
00:10:27,642 --> 00:10:29,683
I'd like to propose a toast...

112
00:10:30,221 --> 00:10:32,398
To Peter's imminent departure...

113
00:10:32,875 --> 00:10:35,148
and his predictable return.

114
00:10:36,389 --> 00:10:38,057
Predictable return.

115
00:10:39,401 --> 00:10:41,578
-Bring everybody luck.
-Okay...

116
00:10:43,216 --> 00:10:44,713
We do this, you see...

117
00:10:44,778 --> 00:10:47,023
every time I give up the game.

118
00:10:47,449 --> 00:10:49,242
[EXCLAIMING]

119
00:10:51,541 --> 00:10:53,269
What was your score, laddie?

120
00:10:55,016 --> 00:10:58,619
Don't bother...I'll keep my own score.
You have your lesson.

121
00:11:00,211 --> 00:11:00,911
I insist.

122
00:11:05,250 --> 00:11:05,750
Um...

123
00:11:06,769 --> 00:11:08,130
a 4 on the 1st...

124
00:11:09,909 --> 00:11:12,536
and a 6 on the 2nd
with that damned bunker.

125
00:11:12,984 --> 00:11:15,093
[SHIVAS] You had a 5 on the 1st.

126
00:11:19,477 --> 00:11:23,082
You must count that one
that you knocked off the tee.

127
00:11:24,169 --> 00:11:25,870
When you had your waggle.

128
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:29,996
So, a 5 and a 6, then?

129
00:11:34,782 --> 00:11:36,006
[SHIVAS] Michael...

130
00:11:37,450 --> 00:11:39,219
you have to remember...

131
00:11:41,043 --> 00:11:46,081
you're in the land where
all these rules were invented.

132
00:11:47,892 --> 00:11:51,021
'Tis the only way you can play in the Kingdom.

133
00:11:56,009 --> 00:11:59,352
You must count that one
that you knocked off the tee.

134
00:12:02,935 --> 00:12:04,704
When you took your waggle.

135
00:12:13,231 --> 00:12:16,582
Can I hit another?
I think that one might be lost.

136
00:12:16,725 --> 00:12:18,154
[SHIVAS] No, not here.

137
00:12:19,401 --> 00:12:22,400
[SHIVAS] You can find it in that particular lot.

138
00:12:30,267 --> 00:12:31,900
[SHIVAS] How does it lie?

139
00:12:34,544 --> 00:12:36,517
[MICHAEL] It fell into a Wynn.

140
00:12:37,070 --> 00:12:39,043
Should I play it or drop out?

141
00:12:40,454 --> 00:12:43,353
[SHIVAS] No, play it as it lies.

142
00:12:44,855 --> 00:12:47,168
[SHIVAS] Always play it as it lies.

143
00:12:47,828 --> 00:12:50,141
[SHIVAS] It'll come out eventually.

144
00:12:54,326 --> 00:12:58,396
[MICHAEL] Play it as it lies...
always play it as it lies.

145
00:12:59,526 --> 00:13:02,723
[MICHAEL](under breath) Holy crap.
[SHIVAS] Huh?

146
00:13:06,621 --> 00:13:10,451
[MICHAEL] I can't even see the damned thing!
I should drop out.

147
00:13:10,794 --> 00:13:14,195
[SHIVAS] Bring me a bouquet
when you come out, yeah?

148
00:13:18,068 --> 00:13:21,401
[SHIVAS] Keep choppin'...
it'll come out eventually.

149
00:13:33,105 --> 00:13:34,738
[MICHAEL] 4 on the 1st...

150
00:13:36,864 --> 00:13:37,952
6 on the 2nd.

151
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:39,444
That damned bunker.

152
00:13:39,509 --> 00:13:42,590
You must count that one that you knocked
off the tee when you took your waggle.

153
00:13:43,893 --> 00:13:45,948
when you took your waggle.

154
00:13:53,131 --> 00:13:55,172
You're makin' a great mistake...

155
00:13:56,170 --> 00:13:57,803
if you think the game...

156
00:13:58,420 --> 00:14:00,121
is meant for the shot.

157
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:08,681
The game is meant for <i>walking</i>.

158
00:14:09,637 --> 00:14:11,066
Old man Key, there...

159
00:14:12,246 --> 00:14:13,607
he showed us how.

160
00:14:15,623 --> 00:14:16,371
With him...

161
00:14:18,185 --> 00:14:23,175
you get the spirit in yourself
to learn to enjoy every step.

162
00:14:25,086 --> 00:14:28,147
I played with him once.
He was 90 years old...

163
00:14:29,683 --> 00:14:31,588
and I'll never forget it.

164
00:14:32,829 --> 00:14:35,197
He sometimes forgot his shots...

165
00:14:35,587 --> 00:14:38,568
the walkin' got to be so good.

166
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,664
That's impossible.

167
00:14:41,066 --> 00:14:44,944
He said he learned to walk
like that from an Indian Yogi...

168
00:14:44,972 --> 00:14:46,128
in the 1880's.

169
00:14:46,447 --> 00:14:48,760
He went on a walk with the Yogi...

170
00:14:49,058 --> 00:14:50,487
in the Himalayas.

171
00:14:51,026 --> 00:14:52,727
And he never got over it.

172
00:14:55,168 --> 00:14:57,073
He said "A walk like that...

173
00:14:57,221 --> 00:15:00,554
was as good for your
soul as a day in church."

174
00:15:00,976 --> 00:15:05,955
And that was somethin' comin' from him
because he was a good Presbyterian.

175
00:15:12,208 --> 00:15:15,813
Noticed you didn't pay much
attention to the walkin'.

176
00:15:18,317 --> 00:15:19,541
I pay attention...

177
00:15:23,508 --> 00:15:24,801
to my next shot.

178
00:15:28,315 --> 00:15:30,016
[SHIVAS] That's too bad...

179
00:15:30,843 --> 00:15:32,476
not enough people do.

180
00:15:34,559 --> 00:15:35,589
It's a shame.

181
00:15:37,265 --> 00:15:39,258
A rotten shame.

182
00:15:41,966 --> 00:15:44,415
Because if you can enjoy the walk...

183
00:15:47,051 --> 00:15:51,065
then perhaps you can enjoy
the other times in your life...

184
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,529
when you're in between.

185
00:15:58,459 --> 00:16:00,364
And that's most of the time.

186
00:16:01,536 --> 00:16:02,692
Couldn't you say?

187
00:16:12,019 --> 00:16:16,101
Michael, just try using your
short irons to finish the hole.

188
00:16:42,986 --> 00:16:47,544
[PETER] First an foremost, we must
all agree it's a mysterious game.

189
00:16:48,206 --> 00:16:51,812
[MICHAEL] You're up.
[PETER] Absurd, on the face of it...

190
00:16:51,881 --> 00:16:55,622
[PETER]...a distraction from
more worthwhile activities.

191
00:16:56,547 --> 00:16:59,268
[PETER] A game, supposedly. A recreation.

192
00:17:00,258 --> 00:17:02,775
[PETER] But 'tis a place of suffering.

193
00:17:02,946 --> 00:17:05,463
[MICHAEL] May I put down another ball?

194
00:17:06,812 --> 00:17:11,434
[PETER] A place that makes a man naked.
An X-ray on the soul.

195
00:17:46,050 --> 00:17:51,900
[SHIVAS] Now try willing it in . It'll never
get there in the regular course of things.

196
00:18:09,197 --> 00:18:11,646
[SHIVAS] Shamus McDuff, as all of you know...

197
00:18:12,782 --> 00:18:15,163
is the man who invented golf ...

198
00:18:16,334 --> 00:18:17,899
all those years ago.

199
00:18:18,946 --> 00:18:24,243
[MICHAEL] He invented golf...that's
[SHIVAS] Invented golf. He's working on it still.

200
00:18:24,306 --> 00:18:30,693
[SHIVAS] And he's blessing Burningbush
by choosing to do his special work <i>here</i>, Peter.

201
00:18:30,727 --> 00:18:35,217
Don't be bringing Shamus McDuff
into this...I can't stand the man.

202
00:18:36,256 --> 00:18:40,066
[SHIVAS] Come on, Peter, Shamus
is our great good friend.

203
00:18:40,074 --> 00:18:41,188
[MICHAEL] Who's Shamus McDuff?

204
00:18:41,213 --> 00:18:43,213
[EVE] Shamus McDuff is the local madman.

205
00:18:43,258 --> 00:18:46,795
[ADAM] Or a very wise man,
depending on your point of view.

206
00:18:46,841 --> 00:18:49,222
[PETER] He's a royal pain in the ass.

207
00:18:49,902 --> 00:18:55,532
Why the city ever consented to let him live in
that ravine off the 13th green, I'll never know.

208
00:18:55,595 --> 00:18:57,801
[MICHAEL] He lives in the ravine?

209
00:18:57,889 --> 00:19:02,013
[SHIVAS] Let's just say he spends a
good deal of his precious time there.

210
00:19:02,094 --> 00:19:06,325
He's constantly studying the
game, working on his theories.

211
00:19:07,402 --> 00:19:08,992
[MICHAEL] What kind of theories?

212
00:19:09,098 --> 00:19:14,405
[LANGE] Well, apparently he's studying gravity...
something he now calls <i>true gravity</i>.

213
00:19:14,952 --> 00:19:19,052
[LANGE] His theory explains the
alignment of human consciousness...

214
00:19:19,121 --> 00:19:22,114
with the physical forces of the universe.

215
00:19:22,274 --> 00:19:24,158
[MICHAEL] So he's a mathematician?

216
00:19:24,222 --> 00:19:30,518
[SHIVAS] In the Pythagorean tradition..
I mean, basically he's had to tip the balance of his mind.

217
00:19:31,174 --> 00:19:33,147
in order to study gravity.

218
00:19:34,196 --> 00:19:42,405
You see, he's floating free now so that
he can get a better <i>fix</i> upon this world of ours.

219
00:19:43,754 --> 00:19:47,206
[HOWLING]
[WHISTLING]

220
00:19:48,902 --> 00:19:52,235
[SHIVAS] How would you like to meet Shamus McDuff?

221
00:19:52,769 --> 00:19:57,688
Come, let us call upon him in the midnight hour.

222
00:20:04,629 --> 00:20:08,638
[SHIVAS] There are animals
here...all <i>sorts</i> of animals.

223
00:20:11,997 --> 00:20:15,603
[HIGH PITCHED HOWLING]
[MICHAEL] What was that?

224
00:20:17,774 --> 00:20:22,386
[HOWLING CONTINUES]
[SHIVAS] That's a Banshee.

225
00:20:22,799 --> 00:20:27,153
[HOWLING CONTINUES]
[SHIVAS] Don't worry. That's just a wee one.

226
00:20:38,707 --> 00:20:41,223
[MICHAEL] Shivas--You wait up?

227
00:20:44,398 --> 00:20:45,442
Shivas!!

228
00:20:52,038 --> 00:20:55,393
[SHIVAS] Michael, where the hell are ya?

229
00:20:56,824 --> 00:20:58,976
[MICHAEL] Something grabbed me down there.

230
00:21:00,482 --> 00:21:01,656
[SHIVAS] Michael...

231
00:21:03,833 --> 00:21:05,466
That's just how it felt.

232
00:21:07,965 --> 00:21:11,196
[SHIVAS] 'Twas a Banshee. They're harmless...

233
00:21:12,075 --> 00:21:13,640
completely harmless.

234
00:21:14,472 --> 00:21:16,409
Except when they're not.

235
00:21:24,545 --> 00:21:30,011
[SHIVAS YELLING]

236
00:21:34,941 --> 00:21:36,595
[MICHAEL] What are you looking for?

237
00:21:36,651 --> 00:21:38,838
[SHIVAS] What do you think?

238
00:21:41,945 --> 00:21:44,326
[SHRIEKING]
[MICHAEL] Jesus Christ!

239
00:21:44,409 --> 00:21:46,254
[SHIVAS] What in the hell is wrong with you now?

240
00:21:46,298 --> 00:21:48,217
[MICHAEL] That sound.
What's that sound?

241
00:21:48,304 --> 00:21:50,698
[SHIVAS] It's coming from the ravine...

242
00:21:50,748 --> 00:21:53,673
it means the coming of the Northern Lights.

243
00:21:59,448 --> 00:22:04,390
