484
00:44:33,297 --> 00:44:34,862
[SHIVAS] Wait them out.

485
00:44:35,837 --> 00:44:39,783
[SHIVAS] I expect you heard
that from your Indian teacher?

486
00:44:43,208 --> 00:44:47,671
[AGATHA] I think the loss of love in
the world is Julian's real despair.

487
00:44:47,776 --> 00:44:50,497
Whatever his philosophizing tells him...

488
00:44:50,611 --> 00:44:54,829
he misses the leisurely pace when
there was time for affection.

489
00:44:54,851 --> 00:44:56,395
Time for reflection.

490
00:44:57,632 --> 00:44:58,731
I miss it too.

491
00:44:59,830 --> 00:45:01,735
We hurry through our days...

492
00:45:25,030 --> 00:45:27,139
[SHIVAS] What are you thinkin'?

493
00:45:30,387 --> 00:45:32,972
[SHIVAS] Tell me what you're thinkin'.

494
00:45:35,992 --> 00:45:38,734
[MICHAEL] This inner body stuff-- it can't last.

495
00:45:39,822 --> 00:45:41,384
It came too easily.

496
00:45:43,935 --> 00:45:50,026
Isn't all this talk of inner bodies and subtle
energies just a device for helping concentration?

497
00:45:51,420 --> 00:45:54,141
[SHIVAS] There are two Michaels I see...

498
00:45:54,924 --> 00:45:57,634
Michael the plunger...

499
00:45:58,291 --> 00:46:00,391
and Michael the doubter.

500
00:46:01,449 --> 00:46:04,782
You can't sit there for more than five minutes...

501
00:46:04,998 --> 00:46:08,202
without your good mind interrupting you.

502
00:46:08,897 --> 00:46:11,482
Watch out for your good mind, Michael.

503
00:46:12,069 --> 00:46:16,371
[MICHAEL] Still, I think any change
in routine would force better concentration.

504
00:46:19,992 --> 00:46:25,073
[MICHAEL] I mean, don't you think Shamus might
be a little<i> off</i>  living in this ungodly ravine?

505
00:46:26,700 --> 00:46:33,095
[SHIVAS] I can see by the way you're talkin'
that the world is not yet ready for Shamus.

506
00:46:33,874 --> 00:46:36,459
[SHIVAS] To swing the man's baffid spoon...

507
00:46:37,739 --> 00:46:39,780
and still to question the man?

508
00:46:47,234 --> 00:46:50,453
[MICHAEL] I guess it doesn't
matter what I think, right?

509
00:46:50,791 --> 00:46:54,995
As long as I feel it. It's the experience
that's the important thing, right?

510
00:47:02,829 --> 00:47:07,341
I mean, look, Shamus is obviously an
incredible person whether he's mad or not.

511
00:47:07,412 --> 00:47:09,657
[SHIVAS] Whether he's mad or not?

512
00:47:09,705 --> 00:47:11,542
It's your world that's mad.

513
00:47:12,197 --> 00:47:13,173
Young man.

514
00:47:13,910 --> 00:47:16,362
Let's go. I can see this has been a mistake.

515
00:47:16,427 --> 00:47:18,768
[MICHAEL] Wait, no. Please...

516
00:47:18,810 --> 00:47:22,055
Please, Shivas. Let's
wait for Shamus.

517
00:47:33,817 --> 00:47:39,055
[SHIVAS] Get off your knees.
You look like you're gonna ask me to marry you.

518
00:48:03,336 --> 00:48:06,588
[MICHAEL] I do want to hear
what you and Shamus talk about.

519
00:48:07,329 --> 00:48:08,309
I really do.

520
00:48:08,678 --> 00:48:11,327
[SHIVAS] The world is not ready yet for Shamus.

521
00:48:11,365 --> 00:48:15,637
[MICHAEL] Yeah, but I'm different.
I mean, this is why I'm going to India to learn about this stuff.

522
00:48:15,731 --> 00:48:18,022
[SHIVAS] The world wasn't
ready for Pythagoras, either.

523
00:48:18,066 --> 00:48:19,414
Pythagoras had the clue.

524
00:48:19,515 --> 00:48:21,333
[MICHAEL] I know all about Pythagoras.

525
00:48:21,516 --> 00:48:26,278
[SHIVAS] You know what you've read
in your books in your fancy school.

526
00:48:38,274 --> 00:48:42,002
[SHIVAS] The world should have
taken its lead from Pythagoras.

527
00:48:43,264 --> 00:48:48,590
To know the world from the
inside, not the outside, as we do.

528
00:48:49,073 --> 00:48:51,998
Like I showed you in the golf shots, there.

529
00:48:55,192 --> 00:48:56,586
True gravity...

530
00:48:58,466 --> 00:49:03,645
that's Shamus' term for the
deeper lanes of forces...

531
00:49:04,944 --> 00:49:07,733
for the deeper structure of the universe.

532
00:49:09,041 --> 00:49:10,061
But this is it.

533
00:49:11,332 --> 00:49:13,931
You have to live into it, yourself.

534
00:49:16,376 --> 00:49:22,628
You can't poke it and shove it the way they
do in the universities and your laboratories...

535
00:49:24,203 --> 00:49:27,060
You must get right into the heart of it...

536
00:49:29,195 --> 00:49:30,607
You must sense it...

537
00:49:32,652 --> 00:49:35,577
through your body, through your feelings...

538
00:49:35,600 --> 00:49:39,137
through your living experience, level after level...

539
00:49:41,167 --> 00:49:43,004
right into the heart of it.

540
00:49:44,457 --> 00:49:49,015
And that's why you won't see me giving any
tips to your golf swings, and these...

541
00:49:49,335 --> 00:49:52,000
how-to books. I won't do it.

542
00:49:52,044 --> 00:49:56,375
Because you have to start from inside yourself.

543
00:49:57,001 --> 00:49:58,294
Like I showed you..

544
00:49:58,627 --> 00:50:02,719
[SHIVAS] Here Michael...swing from your inside.

545
00:50:04,380 --> 00:50:08,962
Go on, from your inner body, Michael.

546
00:50:30,069 --> 00:50:31,770
[SHIVAS] Close your eyes.

547
00:50:42,833 --> 00:50:45,622
Let all your power come from your center.

548
00:50:48,213 --> 00:50:49,181
That's it.

549
00:50:52,215 --> 00:50:53,546
Good.

550
00:51:22,233 --> 00:51:26,751
[AGATHA] Golf is for smellin'
heather and cut grass...

551
00:51:28,755 --> 00:51:31,136
and walking across the countryside.

552
00:51:33,715 --> 00:51:35,416
It's for feelin' the wind...

553
00:51:36,326 --> 00:51:37,959
watchin' the sun go down

554
00:51:39,778 --> 00:51:44,608
It's noticing the splendor of this
good world with every step you take.

555
00:51:46,593 --> 00:51:49,724
[SHIVAS] Good day, chaps...good day.

556
00:51:52,145 --> 00:51:53,506
[SHIVAS] You know...

557
00:51:58,306 --> 00:52:02,274
I've often wondered what it would
be like to play the course...

558
00:52:02,642 --> 00:52:03,935
with the old spoon.

559
00:52:04,772 --> 00:52:08,548
I've often been tempted...
when he's not around.

560
00:52:14,933 --> 00:52:16,294
Why don't we did it?

561
00:52:17,710 --> 00:52:22,083
[MICHAEL] What, you mean now, in the dark?
[SHIVAS] Right now...with one of the featheries.

562
00:52:22,102 --> 00:52:24,211
[MICHAEL] What if we lose them?

563
00:52:29,558 --> 00:52:32,279
[SHIVAS] That's what scares me about it.

564
00:52:52,442 --> 00:52:55,503
[SHIVAS] Do you think that we should do this?

565
00:52:55,784 --> 00:52:58,573
[MICHAEL] Well, I'm not. That's for sure.

566
00:53:02,306 --> 00:53:04,755
[SHIVAS] I think you might be right.

567
00:53:27,052 --> 00:53:28,821
SHIVAS] What do you think?

568
00:53:29,283 --> 00:53:32,048
[MICHAEL] What would Shamus do if you lose the ball?

569
00:53:32,099 --> 00:53:34,072
[SHIVAS] It's not an offer...

570
00:53:36,301 --> 00:53:37,594
What do you think?!

571
00:53:38,917 --> 00:53:41,910
[MICHAEL] Like I said...I'm not hitting any.

572
00:53:45,025 --> 00:53:48,113
[SHIVAS] You go first, I'll
take my line from your shot.

573
00:53:48,176 --> 00:53:49,605
[MICHAEL] No, not me.

574
00:53:49,658 --> 00:53:51,482
[SHIVAS] I'll take my line from your shot.

575
00:53:51,588 --> 00:53:56,700
[SHIVAS BELLOWING]

576
00:53:59,884 --> 00:54:03,762
[SHIVAS] Here, Michael, go.
It'll do you the world of good.

577
00:54:03,826 --> 00:54:04,526
Come on.

578
00:54:04,928 --> 00:54:06,689
Come on, try just once.

579
00:54:07,710 --> 00:54:08,653
Just once.

580
00:54:09,757 --> 00:54:10,581
Just one.

581
00:54:20,612 --> 00:54:21,962
I did it!

582
00:54:22,650 --> 00:54:24,287
I did it!

583
00:54:24,691 --> 00:54:26,596
The old baffin spoon did it!

584
00:54:27,283 --> 00:54:28,732
Yeah!

585
00:54:29,363 --> 00:54:31,132
Come on, come on, come on.

586
00:54:33,478 --> 00:54:35,655
[MICHAEL] Did you see something?

587
00:54:40,487 --> 00:54:41,848
[SHIVAS] You see it?

588
00:54:43,478 --> 00:54:47,077
[MICHAEL] Maybe it fell in the gorse.
[SHIVAS] I don't see it.

589
00:54:49,109 --> 00:54:52,782
[SHIVAS] I hit it over the
green if I hit it anywhere.

590
00:54:58,411 --> 00:55:01,370
[SHIVAS] Oh God...I'll be damned.

591
00:55:03,133 --> 00:55:04,494
[SHIVAS] You see it?

592
00:55:05,488 --> 00:55:08,659
MICHAEL] Shivas...it's in the cup!

593
00:55:10,124 --> 00:55:13,237
Shivas, it's here. It's in the hole!

594
00:55:13,519 --> 00:55:15,016
You got a hole-in-one!

595
00:55:15,960 --> 00:55:17,116
[SHIVAS EXCLAIMS]

596
00:55:35,902 --> 00:55:39,575
[SHIVAS] I never had a
hole-in-one on the 13th before.

597
00:55:47,972 --> 00:55:48,924
Saved my life.

598
00:55:50,288 --> 00:55:52,193
The old spoon saved my life.

599
00:57:22,791 --> 00:57:25,648
[SHIVAS] They're coming from over there...

600
00:57:27,610 --> 00:57:28,698
from the church.

601
00:57:41,154 --> 00:57:47,783
And also, inside of you.

602
00:58:10,358 --> 00:58:17,099
[BALIE] A 77 for Mr. Irons, an 84 for
myself, and for wee lad here--an 86.

603
00:58:17,473 --> 00:58:21,146
And Michael, you had a 34
coming in--same as Mr. Irons...

604
00:58:21,409 --> 00:58:25,213
which just proves that true
gravity works on this plane too.

605
00:58:25,251 --> 00:58:26,612
[MICHAEL] Thank you.

606
00:58:30,902 --> 00:58:33,283
[SHIVAS] See you in the bar, Balie?

607
00:58:43,009 --> 00:58:44,756
[MICHAEL] Can I at least go in Shamus' cave?

608
00:58:44,794 --> 00:58:48,836
[SHIVAS] No. It's as cursed to
strangers as King Tut's tomb.

609
00:58:49,625 --> 00:58:51,734
You might not survive it, Michael.

610
00:59:16,882 --> 00:59:19,976
[SHIVAS] Michael...what you could yell?

611
00:59:21,227 --> 00:59:22,043
Like this...

612
00:59:23,271 --> 00:59:28,834
[SHIVAS YELLING]

613
00:59:32,763 --> 00:59:34,600
[SHIVAS] Try it, just once.

614
00:59:40,163 --> 00:59:41,319
[MICHAEL YELLING]

615
00:59:44,445 --> 00:59:52,932
[SHIVAS] Michael, best way to kill a dragon
is to run right up to it and shove a spear down its throat.

616
01:00:00,085 --> 01:00:05,047
[MICHAEL YELLING]
[SHIVAS YELLING]

617
01:00:25,655 --> 01:00:28,372
[MICHAEL] You seem to know a
lot about Indian philosophy...

618
01:00:29,750 --> 01:00:32,131
you ever thought about going there?

619
01:00:33,763 --> 01:00:34,987
[SHIVAS] To India?

620
01:00:36,746 --> 01:00:37,508
No.

621
01:00:41,394 --> 01:00:43,237
Are you asking me to go with ya?

622
01:00:43,675 --> 01:00:45,104
[MICHAEL] No, I uh...

623
01:00:47,406 --> 01:00:50,580
I was just wondering if you
ever felt the call to go there.

624
01:00:53,496 --> 01:00:56,285
I mean, you're not your typical golf pro.

625
01:00:58,063 --> 01:01:01,668
[SHIVAS] Do you think I
belong in an ashram, Michael?

626
01:01:05,060 --> 01:01:09,260
Do you think I'm like a regular
dues-paying yogi, do ya?

627
01:01:11,015 --> 01:01:13,814
[MICHAEL] Well, yes. Yes, I do.

628
01:01:17,355 --> 01:01:18,898
[SHIVAS] Listen...

629
01:01:28,902 --> 01:01:32,652
Burningbush is my ashram...aye?

630
01:01:34,512 --> 01:01:36,417
And the best place for me...

631
01:01:37,388 --> 01:01:38,344
to practice.

632
01:01:39,846 --> 01:01:41,871
What we glimpsed tonight...

633
01:01:45,038 --> 01:01:47,623
to give something back to the world...

634
01:01:50,970 --> 01:01:55,656
If it's freedom you want, Michael...

635
01:01:57,969 --> 01:02:00,146
if it's freedom that you love...

636
01:02:03,561 --> 01:02:06,079
the whole world can be your ashram.

637
01:02:14,366 --> 01:02:17,397
Let's get some tea, yeah?

638
01:02:46,863 --> 01:02:49,757
[MICHAEL] I'm actually hoping
to be a writer one day.

639
01:02:49,813 --> 01:02:52,550
But right now I'm finishing
up my studies in philosophy.

640
01:02:52,624 --> 01:02:56,434
[LANGE] Well then Murphy, as
an aspiring man of words...

641
01:02:56,688 --> 01:02:59,069
would you tell me whether they have a future?

642
01:02:59,328 --> 01:03:01,097
They've had a dismal past.

643
01:03:07,828 --> 01:03:12,005
[SHIVAS] I do have some...writings. But they're...

644
01:03:13,049 --> 01:03:16,642
they're daft...they're funny writings.

645
01:03:16,696 --> 01:03:19,645
[MICHAEL] I'd love to see anything you've written.
[SHIVAS] No, no, no.

646
01:03:19,766 --> 01:03:22,462
[SHIVAS] They wouldn't be as
polished as you would be used to.

647
01:03:22,513 --> 01:03:23,512
[MICHAEL] I don't care...

648
01:03:23,568 --> 01:03:26,305
[SHIVAS] Nobody's ever seen
them--only Julian and Shamus.

649
01:03:27,932 --> 01:03:29,497
[SHIVAS] Here they are.

650
01:03:33,861 --> 01:03:35,466
[SHIVAS] What do you think?

651
01:03:36,342 --> 01:03:37,977
[MICHAEL] Well, I have to read them first.

652
01:03:38,021 --> 01:03:39,077
[SHIVAS] Of course.

653
01:03:49,707 --> 01:03:51,975
[MICHAEL] Golf is an exercise in perspective...

654
01:03:54,019 --> 01:03:56,074
every shot requires...

655
01:03:57,762 --> 01:04:00,075
that you estimate where you are...

656
01:04:00,391 --> 01:04:02,160
in relation to the target.

657
01:04:04,846 --> 01:04:06,955
Enough golf springs you free...

658
01:04:09,298 --> 01:04:10,318
Free from what?

659
01:04:15,538 --> 01:04:18,582
[SHIVAS] From your attachment to any point.

660
01:04:22,639 --> 01:04:24,633
Somewhere in your brain...

661
01:04:26,491 --> 01:04:29,303
it senses the relativity of things.

662
01:04:34,908 --> 01:04:37,076
Keep askin' the questions, Michael...

663
01:04:37,808 --> 01:04:38,945
The best ones...

664
01:04:39,645 --> 01:04:40,938
don't have answers.

665
01:05:16,096 --> 01:05:18,332
[SHIVAS] Sit, you need a rest.

666
01:05:50,346 --> 01:05:55,535
[SHIVAS] A recipe from Afghanistan.
Brought here by my friends in the Blackwatch.

667
01:06:25,233 --> 01:06:27,410
[SHIVAS] My place of meditation.

668
01:06:44,049 --> 01:06:47,518
[MICHAEL] You know, I have an early train to catch.

669
01:06:53,110 --> 01:06:54,675
How far is the station?

670
01:08:31,072 --> 01:08:32,971
[MICHAEL] Sorry Shivas, I can't stay.

671
01:08:42,198 --> 01:08:43,354
[MICHAEL] Shivas!

672
01:09:14,063 --> 01:09:15,219
[MICHAEL] Shivas!

673
01:09:35,250 --> 01:09:36,080
[MICHAEL] Shivas!

674
01:09:53,222 --> 01:09:54,378
[MICHAEL] Shivas!

675
01:10:01,248 --> 01:10:03,017
[MICHAEL] Shivas, wake up!

676
01:10:04,108 --> 01:10:07,441
[MICHAEL] Shivas, come on, wake up!
Hey, wake up!

677
01:10:41,308 --> 01:10:42,470
Help!

678
01:10:43,564 --> 01:10:44,689
Help!

679
01:11:11,062 --> 01:11:12,456
Somebody's dying!

680
01:11:19,055 --> 01:11:19,867
[MICHAEL] Hello?

681
01:11:19,967 --> 01:11:24,117
[WOMAN] We're havin' a wee bit
of trouble love, just hold on.

682
01:11:25,776 --> 01:11:27,588
[MAN] Hi, what is it?

683
01:11:27,926 --> 01:11:29,763
[MICHAEL] Somebody's dying!

684
01:11:30,284 --> 01:11:31,852
[MAN] Well, what is he dying of, son?

685
01:11:31,972 --> 01:11:35,333
[MICHAEL] I don't know.
Look, I don't know!

686
01:11:37,884 --> 01:11:38,784
[SHIVAS] Michael.

687
01:11:38,903 --> 01:11:39,772
[MICHAEL] Oh God!

688
01:11:39,873 --> 01:11:41,254
[SHIVAS] Tell the I'm fine.

689
01:11:42,407 --> 01:11:43,488
Tell the I'm fine.

690
01:11:44,148 --> 01:11:45,229
[MICHAEL] You scared me.

691
01:11:46,065 --> 01:11:48,310
[MAN] Are you still there? Hello?

692
01:11:49,604 --> 01:11:51,101
[MICHAEL] I'm sorry...

693
01:11:51,788 --> 01:11:53,217
everything's alright.

694
01:11:56,979 --> 01:11:59,088
[SHIVAS] Have I been gone long?

695
01:12:02,406 --> 01:12:03,680
[MICHAEL] I don't know...

696
01:12:04,975 --> 01:12:06,676
but it felt like forever.

697
01:12:08,672 --> 01:12:11,178
[SHIVAS CHANTING]

698
01:12:11,641 --> 01:12:14,294
[MICHAEL] Shit! You scared me to death!

699
01:12:15,187 --> 01:12:18,886
[SHIVAS] Don't you know that we're
just flying here--like kites?

700
01:12:19,668 --> 01:12:22,647
Nothing more than a thread holding...

701
01:12:26,315 --> 01:12:28,220
we're all kites in that way.

702
01:12:30,756 --> 01:12:32,381
We're all kites in that way.

703
01:13:27,285 --> 01:13:29,247
[MICHAEL] I just told you everything's alright.

704
01:14:00,365 --> 01:14:01,715
[MAN] Is that Shamus McDuff?

705
01:14:01,776 --> 01:14:04,905
[WOMAN] That's Evan Tyree, the local champion.

706
01:14:05,043 --> 01:14:07,613
[WOMAN] He's just won a very
important British tournament.

707
01:14:07,707 --> 01:14:10,020
[WOMAN] He's Shivas' most famous pupil.

708
01:14:10,289 --> 01:14:11,214
[MICHAEL] Pay attention.

709
01:14:11,293 --> 01:14:14,586
[EVAN] I'll need my champions
crown if I am to speak.

710
01:14:15,555 --> 01:14:16,967
[EVAN] But I won't speak of golf.

711
01:14:17,013 --> 01:14:18,850
[LANGE] Thank God for that.

712
01:14:19,668 --> 01:14:21,641
[EVAN] I can only tell you...

713
01:14:22,258 --> 01:14:23,414
about my teacher.

714
01:14:24,133 --> 01:14:26,695
[EVAN] For it was he
who showed me the way.

715
01:14:28,097 --> 01:14:30,540
[EVAN] And taught me all
the graces of the game.

716
01:14:31,244 --> 01:14:32,719
This is why you're going to India.

717
01:14:33,084 --> 01:14:36,349
[EVAN] To hold my tempo
between par and bogey...

718
01:14:37,320 --> 01:14:40,934
But moreover, he showed me
the religion of the game.

719
01:14:40,968 --> 01:14:42,042
[SHIVAS] Religion, eh?

720
01:14:42,510 --> 01:14:45,871
[PETER] Shivas, I yield to
you to give the final word.

721
01:14:46,102 --> 01:14:48,546
[SHIVAS] I don't know
anything about the subject.

722
01:14:52,647 --> 01:14:55,098
[LANGE] Enough with these ridiculous excuses.

723
01:14:55,275 --> 01:14:57,588
[SHIVAS] It's to <i>enjoy yourself</i>...

724
01:14:57,826 --> 01:14:59,357
Enjoy yourself.

725
01:14:59,834 --> 01:15:02,928
And beware the quicksands of perfection.

726
01:15:06,190 --> 01:15:07,865
[SHIVAS] Close your eyes, Michael.

727
01:15:08,883 --> 01:15:10,089
Close your eyes.

728
01:15:27,296 --> 01:15:29,191
[SHIVAS] You fancy a drink, do ya?

729
01:15:29,467 --> 01:15:33,533
[SHIVAS] Oh, that's the mad dog.
Takes care of the course--guards the course.

730
01:15:58,932 --> 01:16:00,482
[SHIVAS] I'm against writing...

731
01:16:01,334 --> 01:16:04,665
because of the amount of books
that are already in the world.

732
01:16:08,729 --> 01:16:11,254
[SHIVAS] It's the livin' of
these things that counts...

733
01:16:11,836 --> 01:16:13,129
the livin' of them.

734
01:16:19,850 --> 01:16:22,911
[MICHAEL] Golf is an exercise in perspective.

735
01:16:24,439 --> 01:16:29,761
[MICHAEL] Every shot requires that you estimate
where you are in relation to the target.

736
01:16:31,667 --> 01:16:33,640
Enough golf springs you free.

737
01:16:38,372 --> 01:16:39,534
Free from what?

738
01:16:42,618 --> 01:16:45,042
[SHIVAS] Keep askin' the questions, Michael.

739
01:16:45,438 --> 01:16:48,573
The best ones...don't have answers.

740
01:17:02,026 --> 01:17:03,319
[SHIVAS] That's it.

741
01:19:13,021 --> 01:19:14,815
Just kites in the wind.

742
01:19:38,727 --> 01:19:39,826
Shivas Irons.

743
01:19:42,917 --> 01:19:44,166
Michael Murphy.

744
01:20:02,174 --> 01:20:04,487
[SHIVAS] That's the sound we want.

